original_result.user_prompt: What's VT100 code to render green terminal text?
original_result.completion_text:
The VT100 code to render green terminal text uses the ANSI escape sequence for setting the foreground color to green. In this case, the code is `\033[32m`. When applied within a terminal, it instructs the terminal emulator to display subsequent text in green color until another code resets the color back to default. Below is an illustrative example:

```
\033[32mThis text will appear in green.\033[0m
```

In this example, `\033[32m` sets the color to green, `This text will appear in green.` is what gets displayed in green, and `\033[0m` resets the color back to its original state. This way, only the specified text appears in green while everything else retains their normal colors.
